{"id": "1385", "post": "<div class=\"post-1385 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-virtual-servers tag-fehosting-com tag-openvz tag-scranton tag-tampa tag-uk\" id=\"post-1385\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/foreverhosting-6-30-786mb-openvz-vps/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Forever Hosting \u2013 $6.30 786MB OpenVZ VPS</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/fehosting-com/\" rel=\"tag\">fehosting.com</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/openvz/\" rel=\"tag\">openvz</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/scranton/\" rel=\"tag\">scranton</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/tampa/\" rel=\"tag\">tampa</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/uk/\" rel=\"tag\">uk</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \"> October 13, 2010 @ 11:36 pm, by LowEndAdmin</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><div class=\"notice\"><b>Updated February 2012</b>: Forever Hosting is unfortunately, not forever. It died somewhere in 2011, and it\u2019s homepage has been showing cPanel login page for a while.</div><p><a href=\"http://www.fehosting.com/\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAMPDwwAAACwAAAAAAQABAAACAkQBADs=\" data-src=\"/media/images/fehosting.jpg\" class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"FeHosting\"></a> Via <a href=\"http://www.webhostingtalk.com/showthread.php?t=988696\">this WHT offer</a>. I think <a href=\"http://www.fehosting.com/\"><b>Forever Hosting</b></a> has fixed quite a few confusion on their website and WHMCS <a href=\"/blog/foreverhosting-6-30-512mb-openvz-vps/\">since their last offer</a>, but I am still weary this relative new starter from Canada offering <em>way too much</em> for their cheap VPS promotion. Use the same promo code <b>10OFF</b> to get 10% off recurring discount on their \u201cBudget VPS #1\u201d \u2014 which comes down to <b>$6.30/month</b> (<a href=\"https://secure.fehosting.com/billing/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=21&amp;promocode=10OFF\">sign up link here</a>).</p><ul><li>786MB guaranteed memory (<em>yes, a weird figure</em>)</li><li>20GB storage</li><li>250GB/month data transfer</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li></ul><p>Servers are now available in Scranton PA, Tampa FL, and UK \u2014 although their website remains with HostDime in Orlando FL. From the WHT post you can also request free DirectAdmin license:</p><blockquote><p>If you would like the FREE copy of Directadmin you will need to add it to the order note\u2019s and post the URL to this Ad (<em>note: the WHT link above</em>)!</p></blockquote><p>And free Softaculous license?</p><blockquote><p>Buy any VPS with control panel (cPanel or DirectAdmin) and we will give you a <b>Softaculous license for Free</b>.</p></blockquote><p>It did not state that you need to <em>buy</em> the control panel, but rather <em>buy any VPS</em> with control panel (which DA comes for free) \u2014 thus also qualifies the $6.30/month VPS for free Softaculous? Not that I use any control panel so those would be no use for me, but in theory they might need to honour DA + Softaculous from their ad write-up.</p><p>Domain registered in August. Adjacent NS, and ikr pointed out <a href=\"http://www.webhostingtalk.com/showthread.php?t=985382\">this WHT discussion</a> from our previous post \u2014 seems to be a hosting business with a stormy start.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-